TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {2717=The selections were initially withheld from the public out of fear that the newly formed All-American Football Conference would sign away players selected high.[1] The most notable draft choice in this player selection meeting was made by the Washington Redskins and remains one of the biggest draft blunders of all time. They chose Cal Rossi with the 9th overall pick, but Rossi, a junior at UCLA, was not eligible to be drafted. They chose him again in the 1947 NFL draft, but he never played football professionally., 2119=The 1946 National Football League draft was held on January 14, 1946, at Hotel Commodore in New York.[citation needed]}
